Ford’s China November Sales Fell 7% From Year Earlier to 43,338

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-12-06T06:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/ford-s-china-november-sales-fell-7-from-year-earlier-to-43-338.html
Ford Motor Co. said its November
sales in  China  fell 7 percent from a year earlier to 43,338
vehicles, according to an e-mailed statement.  Deliveries for the first 11 months rose 7 percent to
470,152 vehicles, the statement said. Deliveries at Jiangling
Motors Corp., Ford’s commercial-vehicle joint venture, fell 19
percent to 13,721 vehicles last month, according to the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liza Lin in Shanghai at 
 llin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Young-Sam Cho at 
 ycho2@bloomberg.net  